events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 36 points and led the New Orleans Pelicans to a 114-101 victory over the short-handed Detroit Pistons on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zion Williamson scores 36 as Pelicans send short-handed Pistons to 6th straight loss

headlines.description: — Tobias Harris scored 24 points and Tyrese Maxey added 19 of his 24 in the second half of the Philadelphia 76ers' 121-107 victory over James Harden and the Los Angeles Clippers on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: James Harden and Clippers lose their first meeting with Philadelphia since the trade, 121-107

headlines.description: — There was a 2-on-0 break in the third quarter when Jimmy Butler and Bam Adebayo seemed like they couldn't decide which one was going to get the easy basket.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat build biggest lead in more than a decade, roll past Cavaliers 121-84

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — The Milwaukee Bucks emphatically demonstrated just what they're capable of accomplishing when they have all their top players available.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 30, Middleton gets triple-double as Bucks roll past Thunder 118-93

headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves outlast Warriors 114-110 and match a season high with 21 3-pointers

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 36 points and 16 rebounds, LeBron James added 26 points and 10 assists, and the Los Angeles Lakers produced their franchise's highest-scoring performance in 37 years in a 150-145 victory over the Indiana Pacers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Davis scores 36 points while the Lakers hold off another Pacers comeback in a 150-145 win
